# 🚀 Quick Interview Explanation (4–5 lines version)

> We use prefix sum and a hashmap to store frequency of prefix sums.
> At each index, we check if `prefix_sum - k` exists in the map.
> If it exists, that means we found subarray(s) with sum k.
> This gives O(n) time complexity and works even with negative numbers.



